Rule: If the individual is married, the likelihood of earning more than $50K increases.
If the individual has a Masters or Doctorate degree, the likelihood of earning more than $50K increases.
If the individual is male, the likelihood of earning more than $50K increases.
If the individual works in the Government sector or is a Professional, the likelihood of earning more than $50K increases.
If the individual works significantly more hours per week (e.g., 93 hours), the likelihood of earning more than $50K increases.
If age is reduced from 63 to 58 or 35, the likelihood of earning more than $50K increases.
